#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation steps"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter describes the procedure in which the data for &productname; is "
"copied to the target device. Some basic configuration parameters for the "
"newly installed system are set during the procedure. A graphical user "
"interface will guide you through the installation. <phrase os=\"sles;"
"sled\">The procedure described in the following also applies to remote "
"installation procedures as described in <xref linkend=\"cha-remote-"
"installation\"/>.</phrase> The text-mode installation has the same steps but "
"looks different. <phrase os=\"sles;osuse;slemicro\">For information about "
"performing non-interactive automated installations, see <xref linkend=\"book-"
"autoyast\"/>.</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: date
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:31
#, no-c-format
msgid "2025-02-19"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are a first-time user of &productname;, you should follow the default "
"&yast; proposals in most parts, but you can also adjust the settings as "
"described here to fine-tune your system according to your preferences. Help "
"for each installation step is provided by clicking <guimenu>Help</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation without a mouse"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:46
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the installer does not detect your mouse correctly, use <keycap "
"function=\"tab\"/> for navigation, arrow keys to scroll, and <keycap "
"function=\"enter\"/> to confirm a selection. Various buttons or selection "
"fields contain a letter with an underscore. Use <keycombo><keycap "
"function=\"alt\"/><keycap>Letter</keycap></keycombo> to select a button or a "
"selection directly instead of navigating there with <keycap function=\"tab\"/"
"> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section provides an overview of all installation steps. Each step "
"contains a link to a more detailed description."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At first, &yast; performs network configuration. For details, refer to <xref "
"linkend=\"sec-yast-install-network\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:72
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The actual installation starts with language and keyboard selection and the "
"license agreement. For details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-language-"
"selection\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "Accept the license agreement to proceed to the next step."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&zseries; machines need to activate disks. For details, see <xref "
"linkend=\"sec-yast-install-s390-part\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:90
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Register your system. For details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"registration\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install available extensions. For details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-live-"
"extension\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure NTP servers as described in <xref linkend=\"sec-ntp-"
"configuration\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set a password for the system administrator <literal>root</literal> . For "
"details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-authentication\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The last installation step is an overview of all installation settings. For "
"details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-settings\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After booting into the installation, the installation routine is set up. "
"During this setup, an attempt to configure at least one network interface "
"with DHCP is made. In case this attempt has failed, the <guimenu>Network "
"Settings</guimenu> dialog launches now."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:143
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose a network interface from the list and click <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> "
"to change its settings. Use the tabs to configure DNS and routing. On "
"&zseries; this dialog does not start automatically. It can be started in the "
"<guimenu>Disk Activation</guimenu> step."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:150
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case DHCP was successfully configured during installation setup, you can "
"also access this dialog by clicking <guimenu>Network Configuration</guimenu> "
"at the <guimenu>&scc; Registration</guimenu> and the <guimenu>Installation "
"Settings</guimenu> step. It lets you change the automatically provided "
"settings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:159
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network configuration with boot parameters"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:160
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If at least one network interface has been configured via boot parameters "
"(see <xref linkend=\"sec-boot-parameters-list-network\"/> ), automatic DHCP "
"configuration is disabled and the boot parameter configuration is imported "
"and used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:169
#, no-c-format
msgid "Accessing network storage or local RAID"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To access a SAN or a local RAID during the installation, you can use the "
"libstorage command line client for this purpose:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Switch to a console with <keycombo><keycap function=\"control\"/> <keycap "
"function=\"alt\"/> <keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:182
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the libstoragemgmt extension by running <command>extend "
"libstoragemgmt</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you have access to the <command>lsmcli</command> command. For more "
"information, run <command>lsmcli --help</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:194
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To return to the installer, press <keycombo><keycap function=\"alt\"/> "
"<keycap>F7</keycap></keycombo>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:200
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Supported are Netapp Ontap, all SMI-S compatible SAN providers, and LSI "
"MegaRAID."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:207
#, no-c-format
msgid "Language, Keyboard, and License Agreement"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:210
#, no-c-format
msgid "License agreement"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:221
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guimenu>Language</guimenu> and <guimenu>Keyboard Layout</guimenu> "
"settings are initialized with the language you chose on the boot screen. If "
"you did not change the default, it will be English (US). Change the settings "
"here, if necessary."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:228
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Changing the language will automatically preselect a corresponding keyboard "
"layout. Override this proposal by selecting a different keyboard layout from "
"the drop-down box. Use the <guimenu>Keyboard Test</guimenu> text box to test "
"the layout. The language selected here is also used to assume a time zone "
"for the system clock."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:236
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By clicking <guimenu>Release notes</guimenu> you can access the &slema; "
"release notes in English."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:241
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Read the License Agreement. It is presented in the language you have chosen "
"on the boot screen. Translations are available via the "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>License Translations</guimenu><guimenu>Language</"
"guimenu></menuchoice> drop-down box. If you agree to the terms, check "
"<guimenu>I Agree to the License Terms</guimenu> and click <guimenu>Next</"
"guimenu> to proceed with the installation. If you do not agree to the "
"license agreement, you cannot install &productname;. Click <guimenu>Abort</"
"guimenu> to terminate the installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:254
#, no-c-format
msgid "&zseries;: disk activation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When installing on &zseries; platforms, the language selection dialog is "
"followed by a dialog to configure the attached hard disks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:262
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disk activation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:273
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select DASD, Fibre Channel Attached SCSI Disks (zFCP), or iSCSI for "
"installation of &productname;. The DASD and zFCP configuration buttons are "
"only available if the corresponding devices are attached. <phrase "
"os=\"sles\"> For instructions on how to configure iSCSI disks, refer to "
"<xref linkend=\"sec-iscsi-initiator\"/>.</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also change the <guimenu>Network Configuration</guimenu> in this "
"screen by launching the <guimenu>Network Settings</guimenu> dialog. Choose a "
"network interface from the list and click <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> to change "
"its settings. Use the tabs to configure DNS and routing."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring DASD disks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:294
#, no-c-format
msgid "DASD disk management"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:304
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After selecting <guimenu>Configure DASD Disks</guimenu> , an overview lists "
"all available DASDs. To get a clearer picture of the available devices, use "
"the text box located above the list to specify a range of channels to "
"display. To filter the list according to such a range, select "
"<guimenu>Filter</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:311
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify the DASDs to use for the installation by selecting the corresponding "
"entries in the list. Use <guimenu>Select All</guimenu> to select all DASDs "
"currently displayed. Activate and make the selected DASDs available for the "
"installation by selecting <menuchoice> <guimenu>Perform Action</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Activate</guimenu> </menuchoice> . To format the DASDs, select "
"<menuchoice> <guimenu>Perform Action</guimenu> <guimenu>Format</guimenu> </"
"menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:323
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring zFCP disks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:324
#, no-c-format
msgid "Skip this step if you are not installing on &zseries; hardware."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:328
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configured zFCP Devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:338
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After selecting <guimenu>Configure zFCP Disks</guimenu> , a dialog with a "
"list of the zFCP disks available on the system opens. In this dialog, select "
"<guimenu>Add</guimenu> to open another dialog in which to enter zFCP "
"parameters."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To make a zFCP disk available for the &productname; installation, choose an "
"available <guimenu>Channel Number</guimenu> from the drop-down box. "
"<guimenu>Get WWPNs</guimenu> (World Wide Port Number) and <guimenu>Get LUNs</"
"guimenu> (Logical Unit Number) return lists with available WWPNs and FCP-"
"LUNs, respectively, to choose from. Automatic LUN scanning only works with "
"NPIV enabled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:352
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When completed, exit the zFCP dialog with <guimenu>Next</guimenu> and the "
"general hard disk configuration dialog with <guimenu>Finish</guimenu> to "
"continue with the rest of the configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:363
#, no-c-format
msgid "Registration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:374
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To get technical support and product updates, you need to register and "
"activate &productname; with the &scc; or a local registration server. "
"Registering your product at this stage also grants you immediate access to "
"the update repository. This enables you to install the system with the "
"latest updates and patches available."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:382
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From this dialog, you can switch to the &yast; <guimenu>Network Settings</"
"guimenu> module by clicking <guimenu>Network Configuration</guimenu> .For "
"details, see <xref linkend=\"sec-yast-install-network\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:389
#, no-c-format
msgid "The dialog offers the following possibilities, each described further:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:395
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Register system via scc.suse.com</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:397
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To register with the &scc;, enter the <guimenu>E-mail Address</guimenu> "
"associated with your SCC account and the <guimenu>Registration Code</"
"guimenu> for &productname;. Proceed with <guimenu>Next</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:405
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Register system via local RMT server</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:407
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your organization provides a local registration server, you may "
"alternatively register there. Activate <guimenu>Register System via local "
"RMT Server</guimenu> and either choose a URL from the drop-down box or type "
"in an address. Proceed with <guimenu>Next</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:416
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Skip registration</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:418
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to skip registration or you are offline, click <guimenu>Skip "
"Registration</guimenu> . Accept the warning with <guimenu>OK</guimenu> and "
"proceed with <guimenu>Next</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:424
#, no-c-format
msgid "Skipping registration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:425
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Your system needs to be registered in order to retrieve updates and to be "
"eligible for support. You can register later, after the installation by "
"using <command>SUSEConnect</command> , for details, see <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"images-registration\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:437
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing product patches at installation time"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:438
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After &productname; has been successfully registered, you are asked whether "
"to install the latest available online updates during the installation. If "
"choosing <guimenu>Yes</guimenu> , the system will be installed with the most "
"current packages without having to apply the updates after installation. "
"Activating this option is recommended."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:447
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the system was successfully registered during installation, &yast; will "
"disable repositories from local installation media such as CD/DVD or flash "
"disks when the installation has been completed. This prevents problems if "
"the installation source is no longer available and ensures that you always "
"get the latest updates from the online repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:456
#, no-c-format
msgid "Loading registration codes from USB storage"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:457
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To make the registration more convenient, you can also store your "
"registration codes on a USB storage device such as a flash disk. &yast; will "
"automatically pre-fill the corresponding text box. This is particularly "
"useful when testing the installation or if you need to register many systems "
"or extensions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create a file named <filename>regcodes.txt</filename> or <filename>regcodes."
"xml</filename> on the USB disk. If both are present, the XML takes "
"precedence."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:469
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In that file, identify the product with the name returned by <command>zypper "
"search --type product</command> and assign it a registration code as follows:"
msgstr ""

