#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:506
#, no-c-format
msgid "Extension and Module Selection"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:509
#, no-c-format
msgid "Extensions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:520
#, no-c-format
msgid "&slema; currently offers the following extensions:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:525
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>SUSE Linux Enterprise Live Patching</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:527
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"extension that enables you to apply critical patches without rebooting your "
"system. Bear in mind that you might need an additional subscription on top "
"of the subscription for &slema;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:532
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you enabled the <literal>SUSE Linux Enterprise Live Patching</literal> "
"extension, you need to configure your system as described in <xref "
"linkend=\"pro-completing-KLP-activation\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:538
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Availability of the <literal>SUSE Linux Enterprise Live Patching</literal> "
"extension"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:539
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>SUSE Linux Enterprise Live Patching</literal> extension is "
"available only for the &x86; (except for the real-time kernel) and &zseries; "
"architectures."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:548
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>SUSE Package Hub</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:550
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A free module that provides access to community-maintained packages. "
"Packages in the Package Hub are approved by &suse; for use on &sls;, thus "
"the packages might not be installable on &slema;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:557
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To enable a module, click the corresponding checkbox and then <guimenu>Next</"
"guimenu> to proceed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:563
#, no-c-format
msgid "NTP Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:566
#, no-c-format
msgid "NTP configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:577
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In order to keep time on your system properly synchronized, configure at "
"least one NTP server. You can enter more NTP servers as a comma or space "
"separated list."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:584
#, no-c-format
msgid "Authentication for the System Administrator &rootuser;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:587
#, no-c-format
msgid "Authentication for &rootuser;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:598
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure a strong password for &rootuser;. If your &rootuser; password is "
"randomly generated, use at least 10 characters. If you set your &rootuser; "
"password manually, use a longer password that includes a combination of "
"uppercase and lowercase letters and numbers. The maximum length for "
"passwords is 72 characters, and passwords are case-sensitive."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:606
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to access the system remotely via SSH using a public key, import "
"a key from a removable storage device or an existing partition. To do so "
"click <guimenu>Browse</guimenu> and select the public SSH key."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:612
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Next</guimenu> to proceed to the next installation step."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:620
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:631
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To access a particular setting, click the respective heading. Or some "
"options can be directly changed on the screen by clicking the button next to "
"the option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:638
#, no-c-format
msgid "Partitioning"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:640
#, no-c-format
msgid "Suggested partitioning"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:651
#, no-c-format
msgid "The use of Btrfs and snapshots is mandatory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:652
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&slema; requires Btrfs on the root partition with snapshots and Snapper "
"enabled. Snapper is enabled by default&mdash;do not disable it afterwards."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:659
#, no-c-format
msgid "Custom partitioning on UEFI machines"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:661
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A UEFI machine <emphasis>requires</emphasis> an EFI system partition that "
"must be mounted to <filename>/boot/efi</filename> . This partition must be "
"formatted with the <literal>FAT32</literal> file system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:666
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If an EFI system partition is already present on your system (for example "
"from a previous Windows installation) use it by mounting it to <filename>/"
"boot/efi</filename> without formatting it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:671
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If no EFI system partition is present on your UEFI machine, make sure to "
"create it. The EFI system partition must be a physical partition or RAID 1. "
"Other RAID levels, LVM and other technologies are not supported. It needs to "
"be formatted with the FAT32 file system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:680
#, no-c-format
msgid "Custom partitioning and <systemitem>Snapper</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:682
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the root partition is larger than 12 GB, &productname; by default enables "
"file system snapshots. It is not recommended to use the root partition "
"smaller than 12&nbsp;GB, because it might cause issues when running &slema;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:688
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&productname; uses Snapper together with Btrfs for this feature. Btrfs needs "
"to be set up with snapshots enabled for the root partition."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:692
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Being able to create system snapshots that enable rollbacks requires "
"important system directories to be mounted on a single partition, for "
"example, <filename>/boot</filename> and <filename>/usr</filename> . Only "
"directories that are excluded from snapshots may reside on separate "
"partitions, for example <filename>/usr/local</filename> , <filename>/var</"
"filename> , and <filename>/tmp</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:700
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The installer will automatically create <literal>single</literal> snapshots "
"during and immediately after the installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:705
#, no-c-format
msgid "Btrfs snapshots and root partition size"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:706
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Snapshots may take considerable storage space. Generally, the older a "
"snapshot is or the larger the change set it covers, the more storage space "
"the snapshot takes. And the more snapshots you keep, the more disk space you "
"need."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:712
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To prevent the root partition being filled up with snapshot data, you need "
"to make sure that there is enough space on it. In case you do frequent "
"updates or other installations, consider at least 40&nbsp;GB for the root "
"partition."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:722
#, no-c-format
msgid "Btrfs data volumes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:724
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using Btrfs for data volumes is supported on &productname; &productnumber;. "
"For applications that require Btrfs as a data volume, consider creating a "
"separate file system with quota groups disabled. This is already the default "
"for non-root file systems."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:733
#, no-c-format
msgid "Btrfs on an encrypted root partition"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:735
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default partitioning setup suggests formatting the root partition to "
"Btrfs. To encrypt the root partition, make sure to use the GPT partition "
"table type instead of the MSDOS type. Otherwise the GRUB2 boot loader may "
"not have enough space for the second stage loader."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:744
#, no-c-format
msgid "&zseries;: Using minidisks in z/VM"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:746
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If &productname; is installed on minidisks in z/VM, which reside on the same "
"physical disk, the access path of the minidisks (/dev/disk/by-id/) is not "
"unique. This is because it represents the ID of the physical disk. If two or "
"more minidisks are on the same physical disk, they all have the same ID."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:753
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To avoid problems when mounting minidisks, always mount them either "
"<emphasis>by path</emphasis> or <emphasis>by UUID</emphasis> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:760
#, no-c-format
msgid "&zseries;: LVM root file system"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:762
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you configure the system with a root file system on LVM or software RAID "
"array, you must place <filename>/boot/zipl</filename> on a separate, non-LVM "
"or non-RAID partition, otherwise the system will fail to boot. The "
"recommended size for such a partition is 500&nbsp;MB and the recommended "
"file system is Ext4. Note that <filename>/boot</filename> must be on the "
"same partition as the root file system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:773
#, no-c-format
msgid "Supported software RAID volumes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:775
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Installing to and booting from existing software RAID volumes is supported "
"for Disk Data Format (DDF) volumes and Intel Matrix Storage Manager (IMSM) "
"volumes. IMSM is also known by the following names:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:782
#, no-c-format
msgid "Intel Rapid Storage Technology"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:787
#, no-c-format
msgid "Intel Matrix Storage Technology"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:792
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Intel Application Accelerator / Intel Application Accelerator RAID Edition"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:798
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Intel Virtual RAID on CPU (Intel VROC, see <link xlink:href=\"https://www."
"intel.com/content/www/us/en/support/articles/000024498/memory-and-storage/"
"ssd-software.html\"/> for more details)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:808
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mount points for FCoE and iSCSI devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:810
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"FCoE and iSCSI devices will appear asynchronously during the boot process. "
"While the initrd guarantees that those devices are set up correctly for the "
"root file system, there are no such guarantees for any other file systems or "
"mount points like <filename>/usr</filename> . Hence any system mount points "
"like <filename>/usr</filename> or <filename>/var</filename> are not "
"supported. To use those devices, ensure correct synchronization of the "
"respective services and devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:822
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you need to adjust the partitioning scheme, click the "
"<guimenu>Partitioning</guimenu> menu to open the <guimenu>Suggested "
"partitioning</guimenu> dialog box."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:827
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The installer creates a proposal for one of the available disks containing a "
"root partition formatted with Btrfs and a swap partition. If one or more "
"swap partitions have been detected on the available hard disks, these "
"partitions will be used. You have several options to proceed:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:835
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Accept</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:837
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <guimenu>Accept</guimenu> to accept the proposal without any changes "
"and return to the <guimenu>Installation Settings</guimenu> screen."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:845
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Guided setup</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:847
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To adjust the proposal, choose <guimenu>Guided Setup</guimenu> . First, "
"choose which hard disks and partitions to use. In the <guimenu>Partitioning "
"Scheme</guimenu> screen, you can enable Logical Volume Management (LVM) and "
"activate disk encryption. Afterward specify the <guimenu>Filesystem Options</"
"guimenu> . You can adjust the file system for the root partition and create "
"a separate home and swap partitions. If you plan to suspend your machine, "
"make sure to create a separate swap partition and check <guimenu>Enlarge to "
"RAM Size for Suspend</guimenu> . If the root file system format is Btrfs, "
"you can also enable or disable Btrfs snapshots here."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:862
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Expert Partitioner</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:864
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a custom partition setup, click <guimenu>Expert Partitioner</"
"guimenu> . Select either <guimenu>Start with Current Proposal</guimenu> if "
"you want start with the suggested disk layout, or <guimenu>Start with "
"Existing Partitions</guimenu> to ignore the suggested layout and start with "
"the existing layout on the disk. For details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"slemicro-expert-partitioner\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:878
#, no-c-format
msgid "Expert Partitioner"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:888
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Expert partitioner enables you to set up logical volume management (LVM), "
"configure software RAID and device mapping (DM), encrypt partitions, mount "
"NFS shares and manage tmpfs volumes. To fine-tune settings such as the "
"subvolume and snapshot handling for each Btrfs partition, choose "
"<guimenu>Btrfs</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:895
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All existing or suggested partitions on all connected hard disks are "
"displayed in the left part of the <guimenu>Expert Partitioner</guimenu> "
"dialog. Entire hard disks are listed as devices without numbers, such as "
"<filename>/dev/sda</filename> <phrase arch=\"zseries\"> (or <filename>/dev/"
"dasda</filename>)</phrase> . Partitions are listed as parts of these "
"devices, such as <filename>/dev/sda1</filename> <phrase arch=\"zseries\"> "
"(or <filename>/dev/dasda1</filename>, respectively)</phrase> . The size, "
"type, encryption status, file system, and mount point of the hard disks and "
"their partitions are also displayed. The mount point describes where the "
"partition appears in the Linux file system tree."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:909
#, no-c-format
msgid "Partition tables"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:910
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&productname; allows to use and create different <emphasis>partition tables</"
"emphasis> . In some cases the partition table is called <emphasis>disk "
"label</emphasis> . The partition table is important to the boot process of "
"your computer. To boot your machine from a partition in a newly created "
"partition table, make sure that the table format is supported by the "
"firmware."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:918
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To change the partition table, click the relevant disk name in the left part "
"and choose <menuchoice><guimenu>Device</guimenu> <guimenu>Create New "
"Partition Table</guimenu></menuchoice> . You can create the following "
"partition tables:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:926
#, no-c-format
msgid "Master boot record"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:928
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <emphasis>master boot record (MBR)</emphasis> is the legacy partition "
"table used on IBM PCs. It is sometimes also called an <emphasis>MS-DOS</"
"emphasis> partition table. The MBR only supports four primary partitions. If "
"the disk already has an MBR, &productname; allows you to create additional "
"partitions in it which can be used as the installation target."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:936
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The limit of four partitions can be overcome by creating an "
"<emphasis>extended partition</emphasis> . The extended partition itself is a "
"primary partition and can contain more <emphasis>logical partitions</"
"emphasis> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:945
#, no-c-format
msgid "GPT partition table"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:947
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"UEFI computers use a <emphasis>GUID Partition Table</emphasis> (GPT) by "
"default. &productname; will create a GPT on a disk if no other partition "
"table exists."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:952
#, no-c-format
msgid "Old BIOS firmware does not support booting from GPT partitions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:955
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You need a GPT partition table to use more than four primary partitions, "
"UEFI Secure Boot or use disks larger than 2&nbsp;TB."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:964
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating partitions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:965
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The expert partitioner enables you to add partitions. Bear in mind that the "
"root file system must be formatted to Btrfs and snapshots must be enabled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:970
#, no-c-format
msgid "The procedure below creates a Btrfs partition with enabled snapshots."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:975
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the desired hard disk in the left part and click <guimenu>Add "
"Partition</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:981
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define size of the partition or define the region of disk for the partition. "
"Proceed with <guimenu>Next</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

