#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1184
#, no-c-format
msgid "Software"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1186
#, no-c-format
msgid "Software configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1196
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&productname; contains several software patterns for various application "
"purposes. Click <guimenu>Software</guimenu> to open the <guimenu>Software "
"Selection and System Tasks</guimenu> screen where you can modify the pattern "
"selection according to your needs. Select a pattern from the list and see a "
"description in the right-hand part of the window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1203
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this menu you can select the <literal>Web based remote system management</"
"literal> pattern that will install <literal>Cockpit</literal> system. "
"Cockpit is a web monitoring tool that enables you to administer your system. "
"For details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-admin-cockpit\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1209
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can also select the <literal>KVM Virtualization Host</literal> "
"pattern to install packages required to run &slema; as a &kvm; host server "
"(&xen; is not supported). However, you should consider the limitations of "
"&slema; running as a &kvm; host server; for details, refer to <link xlink:"
"href=\"https://documentation.suse.com/sles/15-SP3/html/SLES-all/cha-virt-"
"support.html\">virtualization limits and support</link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each pattern contains several software packages needed for specific "
"functions (for example Podman). For a more detailed selection based on "
"software packages to install, select <guimenu>Details</guimenu> to switch to "
"the &yast; Software Manager."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1226
#, no-c-format
msgid "Timezone"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1228
#, no-c-format
msgid "Time zone configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1238
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, the time is synchronized by using the NTP servers you provided "
"in the previous steps of the installation procedure. You can select the "
"region and time zone either by clicking a particular place on the map or by "
"selecting a region and time zone in the drop-down menus."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1245
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the hardware clock to UTC"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The switch from standard time to daylight saving time (and vice versa) can "
"only be performed automatically when the hardware clock (CMOS clock) is set "
"to UTC. This also applies if you use automatic time synchronization with "
"NTP, because automatic synchronization will only be performed if the time "
"difference between the hardware and system clock is less than 15 minutes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1254
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since a wrong system time can cause serious problems, it is strongly "
"recommended to <emphasis>always</emphasis> set the hardware clock to UTC."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The button <guimenu>Other settings</guimenu> enables you to set the date and "
"time manually or configure NTP servers synchronization."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to set the time and date manually, click the <guimenu>Other "
"settings</guimenu> button and select <guimenu>Manually</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1268
#, no-c-format
msgid "Time cannot be changed on &zseries;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1269
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since the operating system is not allowed to change time and date directly, "
"the <guimenu>Other Settings</guimenu> option is not available on &zseries;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1278
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1279
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Network is automatically configured at the beginning of the installation "
"process, but if it is necessary you can change the configuration by clicking "
"<guimenu>Network Configuration</guimenu> . A dialog box opens, for details "
"refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-yast-install-network\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1285
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&slema; uses &nm; by default, but you can switch to <command>wicked</"
"command> by clicking <guimenu>switch to wicked</guimenu> . Bear in mind that "
"after the installation is complete, you cannot switch the network managing "
"service to &nm;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1293
#, no-c-format
msgid "Booting"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The installer proposes a boot configuration for your system. Other operating "
"systems found on your computer, such as Microsoft Windows or other Linux "
"installations, will automatically be detected and added to the boot loader. "
"However, &productname; will be booted by default. Normally, you can leave "
"these settings unchanged. If you need a custom setup, modify the proposal "
"according to your needs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1312
#, no-c-format
msgid "Software RAID 1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Booting a configuration where <filename>/boot</filename> resides on a "
"software RAID 1 device is supported, but it requires installing the boot "
"loader into the MBR ( <menuchoice> <guimenu>Boot Loader Location</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Boot from Master Boot Record</guimenu> </menuchoice> ). Having "
"<filename>/boot</filename> on software RAID devices with a level other than "
"RAID 1 is not supported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1325
#, no-c-format
msgid "Kdump"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1327
#, no-c-format
msgid "Kdump configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1337
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using Kdump, you can save a dump of the kernel (in case of a crash) to "
"analyze what went wrong. By default, Kdump is enabled. By clicking "
"<guimenu>Kdump</guimenu> you open a dialog box for configuring Kdump."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1344
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start-Up"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1346
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can disable Kdump and configure the amount of memory reserved for "
"Kdump. Usually you do not have to change the prefilled values."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1353
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dump Filtering"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1355
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Dump filtering enables you to select which pages will be included in the "
"Kdump, and to define the format of of Kdump."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1362
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dump Target"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can select a local directory or you can save KDump to a remote location. "
"If you prefer a remote location, you also need to configure connection "
"details according to the respective protocol."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1372
#, no-c-format
msgid "Email Notifications"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1374
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To receive email notifications if an event occurs, specify an email address."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1381
#, no-c-format
msgid "Expert Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1383
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option enables you to define command-line parameters, custom kernel "
"dump and other advanced settings related to Kdump."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1393
#, no-c-format
msgid "System"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1395
#, no-c-format
msgid "System overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1405
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This screen lists all the hardware information the installer could obtain "
"about your computer. When opened for the first time, the hardware detection "
"is started. Depending on your system, this may take some time. Select any "
"item in the list and click <guimenu>Details</guimenu> to see detailed "
"information about the selected item. Use <guimenu>Save to File</guimenu> to "
"save a detailed list to either the local file system or a removable device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1413
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Advanced users can also change the <guimenu>PCI ID Setup</guimenu> and "
"kernel settings by choosing <guimenu>Kernel Settings</guimenu> . A screen "
"with two tabs opens:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1420
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>PCI ID setup</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each kernel driver contains a list of device IDs of all devices it supports. "
"If a new device is not in any driver's database, the device is treated as "
"unsupported, even if it can be used with an existing driver. You can add PCI "
"IDs to a device driver here. Only advanced users should attempt to do so."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1429
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add an ID, click <guimenu>Add</guimenu> and select whether to "
"<guimenu>Manually</guimenu> enter the data, or whether to choose from a "
"list. Enter the required data. The <guimenu>SysFS Dir</guimenu> is the "
"directory name from <filename>/sys/bus/pci/drivers</filename> &mdash;if "
"empty, the <guimenu>driver</guimenu> name is used as the directory name. "
"Existing entries can be managed with <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> and "
"<guimenu>Delete</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1441
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Kernel settings</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1443
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Activating the <guimenu>Enable SysRq Keys</guimenu> item, will let you issue "
"basic commands (such as rebooting the system or writing kernel dumps) in "
"case the system crashes. Enabling these keys is recommended when doing "
"kernel development. Refer to <link xlink:href=\"https://www.kernel.org/doc/"
"html/latest/admin-guide/sysrq.html\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1457
#, no-c-format
msgid "Security"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1459
#, no-c-format
msgid "Security configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1470
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not use firewall along with Podman"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1471
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using firewall along with Podman may result in missing Podman-related "
"firewall rules after reloading the <literal>firewalld</literal> service. "
"Therefore, it is recommended to keep the firewall in its default setting "
"(disabled) if you intend to use Podman."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1478
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can enable the firewall or disable the SSH service directly by clicking "
"the respective button. Clicking on the button next to <guimenu>CPU "
"mitigations</guimenu> opens the <guimenu>Boot Loader Settings</guimenu> "
"dialog box, where you can change kernel parameters including the "
"<literal>CPU mitigations</literal> configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1485
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guimenu>CPU Mitigations</guimenu> refer to kernel boot command line "
"parameters for software mitigations that have been deployed to prevent CPU "
"side-channel attacks. You can configure the following values:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1492
#, no-c-format
msgid "Auto"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1494
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All CPU side channel mitigations are enabled as they are detected based on "
"the CPU type. The auto-detection handles both unaffected older CPUs and "
"unaffected newly released CPUs and transparently disables mitigations. This "
"options leave SMT enabled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1503
#, no-c-format
msgid "Off"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1505
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All CPU side channel mitigations are disabled. While this option gives the "
"higher performance, it also bears the highest risk. Do not use this setting "
"where there is a risk of untrusted code."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1513
#, no-c-format
msgid "Auto + No Smt"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1515
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All CPU side channel mitigations are enabled as they are detected based on "
"the CPU type. Additionally the symmetric multi-threading of the CPU is "
"disabled if necessary, for instance to mitigate the L1 Terminal Fault side "
"channel issue."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1524
#, no-c-format
msgid "Manually"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1526
#, no-c-format
msgid "CPU mitigations are detected manually."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1532
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, the firewall is disabled. Click <guimenu>enable</guimenu> to "
"change the default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1536
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The SSH service is enabled by default. Click <guimenu>disable</guimenu> to "
"change the setting. If you disable the SSH service, you will not be able to "
"login to your system remotely. The SSH port (22) is open by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1541
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default &selnx; option is <guimenu>enforcing</guimenu> . You can change "
"the value by clicking <guimenu>Security</guimenu> and selecting another "
"option in the <guimenu>Mode</guimenu> menu."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_manual_installation.xml:1546
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <guimenu>Security</guimenu> dialog box, you can also select PolicyKit "
"privileges in the <guimenu>PolicyKit Default Privileges</guimenu> dropdown "
"menu."
msgstr ""
